benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search/{searchKey} - Search custom fields

covered: Valid GET requests: Happy path tested with required path parameter and multiple query parameter combinations (limit, offset, audit).
Empty Response: Scenarios cover zero matches returning an empty JSON array (TC06, TC09).
Pagination: Multiple tests validate paging behavior and boundaries (TC02, TC07, TC09, TC28).
Query Parameters: Broad coverage of valid/invalid parameter combinations including limit, offset, audit, and ignoring unsupported params (TC10-14, TC28, TC29).
Authorization: Tests verify 401 for missing and invalid tokens (TC15, TC16).
Audit variations: FULL, MINIMAL, NONE and combinations with pagination (TC03, TC04, TC05, TC28).
Backwards compatibility: Legacy path usage without query parameters (TC22).
Integration/data consistency: Test ensures data reflects integration with external services (TC23).
Accessibility/error messages: Tests review of descriptive errors and API docs (TC24).
Edge cases and input validation: Special characters (TC18), whitespace/unusual input (TC25), Unicode (TC27), and max length boundary (TC26).
Performance and concurrency: Stress test (TC19) and concurrent requests (TC20).
gaps: Rate limiting: No tests validating rate limiting or throttling under load.
Caching behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache semantics.
Authorization edge-case: No test for 403 Forbidden due to insufficient permissions.
Internal server error coverage: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error test; only 503 service unavailability is covered.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to verify throttling/throughput behavior under burst traffic.
Add caching tests to validate ETag/Cache-Control headers and cache invalidation semantics.
Add a test for 403 Forbidden to cover insufficient permissions scenarios in addition to 401.
Add test for 500 Internal Server Error or simulate database failures to validate server-side error handling and payloads.
